      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cli): reject finite-but-unsafe byte sizes",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n`parseByteSize` (`src/cli/parse-bytes.ts`) computed `Math.round(value * multiplier)` and guarded only with `if (!Number.isFinite(bytes))`. For inputs above `Number.MAX_SAFE_INTEGER` the result is **finite but not a safe integer**, so the guard passed and the function silently returned a precision-corrupted value — e.g. `parseByteSize(\"9007199254740993\")` returned `9007199254740992` (a different number than typed) and `parseByteSize(\"9000000tb\")` returned `9895604649984000000`.\n\nIts direct sibling `parseDurationMs` (`src/cli/parse-duration.ts`) was changed in commit `35cdd40182` (\"fix(cli): reject unsafe duration values\") from the identical `Number.isFinite` check to a `roundSafeDurationMs` helper that throws on `!Number.isSafeInteger`. `parse-bytes.ts` is the twin left on the old, now-known-buggy contract. `parseByteSize` is consumed on config-validation/runtime paths (`config/zod-schema.ts` runLog.maxBytes, session maxDiskBytes/highWaterBytes, `cron/run-log.ts`).\n\n### Changes\n- `parse-bytes.ts` — add `roundSafeByteSize(raw, value)` that throws via the existing `invalidByteSize` when the rounded result is not a safe integer, mirroring `roundSafeDurationMs`. `Number.isSafeInteger` also covers the non-finite case the old guard handled.\n- `cli-utils.test.ts` — finite-but-unsafe cases.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: byte sizes above `Number.MAX_SAFE_INTEGER` were accepted and returned precision-corrupted instead of being rejected. After the fix they throw; valid sizes are unchanged.\n\nReal environment tested: Node 22.22.1, macOS, no network/model. Vitest exercises the real exported `parseByteSize`. BEFORE is `origin/main`'s file (swapped via `git show`).\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/cli/cli-utils.test.ts\n```\n\nEvidence after fix:\n```\nparseByteSize(\"9007199254740993\")  BEFORE: 9007199254740992 (corrupted)   AFTER: throws \"Invalid byte size\"\nparseByteSize(\"9000000tb\")         BEFORE: 9895604649984000000 (corrupted) AFTER: throws \"Invalid byte size\"\nparseByteSize(\"10mb\")              BOTH: 10485760  (valid, unchanged)\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: out-of-safe-range sizes are rejected; all existing valid/invalid cases are unchanged. The new tests fail on `origin/main` and pass after.\n\nWhat was not tested: end-to-end config validation (the test drives the real exported `parseByteSize` those schemas call).\n\n## Additional checks\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/cli/cli-utils.test.ts` passes; fail-before verified by swapping in `origin/main`'s file. `oxlint --tsconfig` clean.\n",
        "branch": "fix/parse-bytes-unsafe-integer",
